# Frontend Conventions

## Language & Style
- React 19 + Vite 6, JavaScript (JSX) — no TypeScript
- Tailwind v4 utility classes; prefer semantic token names over raw values
- shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/` — never modify installed components directly; wrap them
- All paths aliased through `@/` → `src/`
- `async/await` everywhere; no `.then()` chains
- No `console.log` in committed code

## Component rules
- One component per file; filename matches the component name (`JobCard.jsx`)
- Pages live in `src/pages/`, reusable components in `src/components/`
- Shared UI primitives (shadcn copies) live in `src/components/ui/`
- Keep pages thin — data fetching via TanStack Query hooks in `src/lib/queries.js`

## Data fetching
- All API calls go through `src/lib/api.js` (axios instance); never call `fetch` directly
- Use `useQuery` / `useMutation` from `@tanstack/react-query` for all server state
- Leaderboard and batch status polls use `refetchInterval` on the query

## Styling
- Brand tokens live in `src/styles/tokens.css` (imported in `main.css`)
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Never use inline `style={{}}` except for dynamic/computed values (e.g. score bar widths)

## Commands
```bash
cd frontend
npm install      # install deps
npm run dev      # start dev server (default :5173)
npm run build    # production build
npm run lint     # eslint
npm run preview  # preview production build
```
